S. Africa Minister to Seek Ruling on Mine Zoning, Bus. Day Says

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-09-27T05:33:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/s-africa-minister-to-seek-ruling-on-mine-zoning-bus-day-says.html
South African Mineral Resources
Minister Susan Shabangu plans to get a Constitutional Court
ruling on whether municipalities can regulate mining zoning
after the  Supreme Court  of Appeal ruled on Sept. 23 local
government has this power, Business Day said, citing spokesman
 Bheki Khumalo .  Few South African mines held the proper zoning licenses
under local-planning rules, the Johannesburg-based newspaper
cited Melissa Fourie, director of the Centre for Environmental
Rights, as saying.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  